timeline.bodyText:
you are using this overload ...
StatusUtils.setStatusConditionAndObservedGeneration(R resource, S status, String type, String conditionStatus, Throwable error)
where conditionStatus is actually always "True".
Maybe it could be useful having another overload without the conditionStatus where it's set to "True" implicitly.
Something like we already have:
public static <R extends CustomResource, S extends Status> void setStatusConditionAndObservedGeneration(R resource, S status, Throwable error) {
        setStatusConditionAndObservedGeneration(resource, status, error == null ? "Ready" : "NotReady", "True", error);
    }
but with the additional type parameter.

